title: He Has Called Me

tokens.lyric: The Lord has called and I will go, where He leads me I will follow;

lines.raw: [Eb]The Lord has called and I will go, where He leads me I will follow;

tokens.lyric: The same in sorrow as in joy; with one heart I follow my Lord.

lines.raw: [Ab]The same in sorrow as in joy; with one heart I follow my Lord.

tokens.lyric: For none on earth can turn me back, not even death can stop me,

lines.raw: [Eb]For none on earth can turn me back, not even death can stop me,

tokens.lyric: No none on earth can turn me back, not even death can stop me.

lines.raw: [Ab]No none on earth can turn me back, not even death can stop me.

tokens.lyric: To barren valleys piled with bones, I will take the living message;

lines.raw: [Bb]To barren valleys piled with bones, I will take the living message;

tokens.lyric: To Sodom's foul and wretched streets, I will bear the word with love.

lines.raw: [F7]To Sodom's foul and wretched streets, I will bear the word with love.

tokens.lyric: I bind my heart, my life to Yours, that it may be an offering,

lines.raw: [Bb]I bind my heart, my life to Yours, that it may be an offering,

tokens.lyric: I bind my heart, my life to Yours, that it may be an offering.

lines.raw: [Bb]I bind my heart, my life to Yours, that it may be an offering.

tokens.lyric: To You belongs our full acclaim, all glory power and honor,

lines.raw: [Eb]To You belongs our full acclaim, all glory power and honor,

tokens.lyric: The world's contempt I do not fear, I will gladly bear the cross.

lines.raw: [Ab]The world's contempt I do not fear, I will gladly bear the cross.

tokens.lyric: Without esteem, without renown, I only wish to follow,

lines.raw: [Bb]Without esteem, without renown, I only wish to follow,

tokens.lyric: Without esteem, without renown, I only wish to follow.

lines.raw: [Bb]Without esteem, without renown, I only wish to follow.
